s why he\'s failing. And why you\'re a liability.\n\n**CLIFFHANGER / EPISODE END**\n[Leila stares at the closed box, the viper symbol seeming to pulse malevolently. Leila\'s reflection is distorted in the glass, her face pale with horror. Gabriel\'s hand reaches out, closing the box. He looks at Leila, his gaze unwavering, but a flicker of something akin to regret crosses his face. He knows what she\'s thinking. He knows what this implies. The final image is the closed box, the viper symbol the last thing we see, leaving Leila to wonder if Gabriel is preparing to protect her, or to make her disappear himself.]\n\n## EPISODE 27 — The Viper\'s Warning\n*Duration target: 120–180 seconds*\n\n**COLD OPEN (0:00–0:15)**\n[CLOSE UP on a small, ornate wooden box, intricately carved with a viper symbol. Gabriel\'s hands open it slowly. Inside, nestled on black velvet, is a single, venomous-looking fangs. Leila\'s reflection is distorted in the polished wood, her face pale with horror.]\n\n**SCENE 1 — THE BOX\'S CONTENTS**\n[INT. ABANDONED WAREHOUSE - NIGHT]\n\nLEILA\n(whispering)\nWhat is that?\n\nGabriel closes the box with a soft snap. He doesn\'t look at her.\n\nGABRIEL\nA warning. From a very old friend of Julian\'s.\n\nLEILA\n(confused)\nA warning? For who? For Julian?\n\nGabriel finally meets her eyes. His gaze is heavy, unreadable.\n\nGABRIEL\nFor anyone who crosses him. Or anyone he wants to disappear.\n\n[Leila shivers, a cold dread seeping into her bones. The implications are clear.]\n\n**SCENE 2 — THE POISON\'S PROMISE**\n[INT. ABANDONED WAREHOUSE - NIGHT]\n\nLeila stares at the closed box, the viper symbol seeming to pulse malevolently.\n\nLEILA\nHe sent this to... to threaten us?\n\nGABRIEL\n(nods slowly)\nOr to remind me of what he\'s capable of. This isn\'t just a symbol, Leila. It\'s a signature. A promise.\n\nHe picks up the box, turning it over in his hands.\n\nGABRIEL (CONT\'D)\nThe man who uses this... he doesn\'t leave loose ends.\n\n[Leila\'s eyes widen, a new layer of fear settling in. This isn\'t just about Julian anymore. It\'s about a network far more dangerous.]\n\n**SCENE 3 — A FAMILIAR SCENT**\n[INT. ABANDONED WAREHOUSE - NIGHT]\n\nLeila watches Gabriel, her mind racing.\n\nLEILA\nYou know him, don\'t you? The man with the viper.\n\nGabriel hesitates, a flicker of something akin to regret crossing his face.\n\nGABRIEL\nWe\'ve... crossed paths. In a different life.\n\nLeila steps closer, a sudden realization dawning on her. She remembers the faint, metallic scent she\'d occasionally caught on Julian\'s clothes, a scent she could never quite place.\n\nLEILA\n(softly)\nThat smell... I\'ve smelled it before. On Julian. Like old metal, and something sweet, sickly.\n\nGabriel\'s head snaps up, his eyes locking onto hers. He recognizes the description.\n\nGABRIEL\n(low, urgent)\nWhere? When?\n\n[Leila\'s memory flashes to a specific evening, a gala, Julian returning from a private meeting.]\n\n**SCENE 4 — THE ART OF DISAPPEARANCE**\n[INT. ABANDONED WAREHOUSE - NIGHT]\n\nLEILA\nA few months ago. After a private meeting Julian had. He said it was with a new investor... but he was agitated. And he had that smell.\n\nGabriel\'s jaw tightens. He places the box back on the table.\n\nGABRIEL\nThis isn\'t just a warning, Leila. It\'s a message. He\'s telling me he knows I\'m involved. And that he knows how to make people disappear without a trace. He\'s one of the best.\n\nLEILA\n(horrified)\nMake people disappear...?\n\nGABRIEL\n(grimly)\nPermanently. And silently.\n\n[Leila looks from Gabriel to the viper box, then back to Gabriel, a chilling realization forming: Gabriel isn\'t just protecting her from Julian, but from this far more insidious threat that Julian is connected to. The stakes have just escalated beyond anything she imagined.]\n\n**CLIFFHANGER / EPISODE END**\n[CLOSE UP on the viper box. Gabriel\'s hand reaches out, slowly closing the lid, the viper symbol the last thing we see. Leila\'s reflection is distorted in the glass, her face pale with horror. Gabriel\'s hand reaches out, closing the box. He looks at Leila, his gaze unwavering, but a flicker of something akin to regret crosses his face. He knows what she\'s thinking. He knows what this implies. The final image is the closed box, the viper symbol the last thing we see, leaving Leila to wonder if Gabriel is preparing to protect her, or to make her disappear himself.]\n\n## EPISODE 28 — The Viper\'s Embrace\n\n**COLD OPEN (0:00–0:15)**\n[CLOSE UP on a small, ornate wooden box. A hand, GABRIEL\'S, slowly opens the lid, revealing a coiled, silver viper symbol etched into the velvet lining. LEILA\'S reflection is distorted in the glass, her face pale with horror.]\n\n**SCENE 1 — THE BOX\'S SECRET**\n[INT. ABANDONED WAREHOUSE - NIGHT]\n\nLEILA\n(whispering)\nWhat is that?\n\nGabriel closes the box quickly, almost instinctively. He looks at Leila, his gaze unwavering, but a flicker of something akin to regret crosses his face. He knows what she\'s thinking. He knows what this implies.\n\nGABRIEL\nIt\'s a symbol. Nothing more.\n\nLEILA\nNothing more? It\'s a viper. And you just... hid it. Like a secret.\n\nGabriel sighs, running a hand through his hair.\n\nGABRIEL\nIt belonged to someone I used to know. Someone dangerous.\n\nLEILA\n(scoffs)\nMore dangerous than Julian?\n\nGabriel\'s eyes darken. He picks up the box again, turning it over in his hands.\n\nGABRIEL\nJulian is a wolf in sheep\'s clothing. This... this is the wolf that hunts wolves.\n\nLeila shivers, despite herself.\n\n**SCENE 2 — A FATHER\'S LEGACY**\n[INT. ABANDONED WAREHOUSE - NIGHT]\n\nLeila watches Gabriel, her mind racing.\n\nLEILA\nMy father... he had a collection of antique weapons. Hidden. I always thought it was just a hobby. A strange one.\n\nGabriel pauses, looking at her.\n\nGABRIEL\nWhat kind of weapons?\n\nLEILA\nDaggers. Swords. But there was one box... always locked. Carved with a symbol. I never saw it clearly, but...\n\nShe trails off, her eyes wide.\n\nLEILA (CONT\'D)\nIt was a snake. A viper.\n\nGabriel\'s grip tightens on the box in his hands. The pieces are starting to fit, forming a terrifying picture.\n\nGABRIEL\nYour father... he wasn\'t just a collector.\n\n**SCENE 3 — THE PROTECTOR\'S MARK**\n[INT. ABANDONED WAREHOUSE - NIGHT]\n\nLeila stares at Gabriel, a dawning horror in her eyes.\n\nLEILA\nAre you saying... my father was involved with people like that? With... vipers?\n\nGABRIEL\nThe viper symbol isn\'t just a mark of danger, Leila. It\'s a mark of protection. A very specific, very brutal kind of protection. For those who can afford it. Or those who are born into it.\n\nHe looks at her, a new understanding in his gaze.\n\nGABRIEL (CONT\'D)\nYour family. The Armans. They\'ve been part of this network for generations, haven\'t they?\n\nLeila shakes her head, tears welling in her eyes. The gilded cage was far more dangerous than she ever imagined.\n\nLEILA\nI don\'t... I don\'t know anything about this.\n\n**CLIFFHANGER / EPISODE END**\n[Gabriel opens the small wooden box again, revealing the silver viper. He then reaches into his pocket and pulls out a small, tarnished silver charm on a chain. It’s the exact same viper symbol. He holds it out to Leila, his face grim, the implication heavy in the air: he is one of them, or was, and her family\'s secrets run deeper than she could ever comprehend.]\n\n## EPISODE 29 — The Viper\'s Mark\n\n**COLD OPEN (0:00–0:15)**\n[Leila stares at the silver viper symbol on the small wooden box. Gabriel holds out a tarnished silver charm on a chain, identical to the viper. His face is grim, unreadable.]\n\n**SCENE 1 — THE UNSETTLING RECOGNITION**\n[Leila recoils slightly, her gaze darting between the viper on the box and the charm in Gabriel\'s hand. Her breath hitches.]\nLEILA\n(whispering)\nWhat is this? What does this mean?\n\nGABRIEL\n(voice low, rough)\nIt means your family\'s history is... complicated. More complicated than you know.\n\n[Leila shakes her head, a desperate denial. Gabriel\'s eyes never leave hers, a silent challenge.]\n\n**SCENE 2 — A FAMILY\'S SHADOW**\n[Gabriel slowly closes his hand around the charm, concealing it. He gestures to the wooden box.]\nGABRIEL\nThis symbol... it\'s old. Older than Julian\'s games. It belongs to a society. A very exclusive one.\n\nLEILA\n(confused)\nMy family... they\'re involved in some kind of society? What are you talking about?\n\nGABRIEL\nThey call themselves \'The Serpent\'s Coil\'. Your grandmother, your father... they were prominent members.\n\n[Leila stares, disbelief warring with a dawning, terrible understanding. The opulent room suddenly feels cold, menacing.]\n\n**SCENE 3 — GABRIEL\'S PAST CONNECTION**\n[Leila takes a step back, her eyes wide with a new kind of fear.]\nLEILA\nAnd you? How do you know about this? Why do you have that charm?\n\n[Gabriel hesitates, a flicker of pain in his eyes. He looks away, then back at her, a decision made.]\nGABRIEL\nI was... recruited. Years ago. Before I understood what it truly was. It\'s how I know so much about their methods, their networks.\n\nLEILA\n(voice trembling)\nYou were one of them?\n\n[Gabriel nods slowly, his jaw tight. The weight of his past hangs heavy in the air between them.]\n\n**CLIFFHANGER / EPISODE END**\n[Leila looks at Gabriel, a man she thought she was beginning to understand, now revealed as having a profound, disturbing connection to her family\'s darkest secrets. She glances at the viper symbol on the box, then back to Gabriel, a chilling thought forming: if he was part of this, what else is he hiding, and how deep does her family\'s complicity truly run?]\n\n## EPISODE 30 — The Frame Up\n\n**COLD OPEN (0:00–0:15)**\n[A news headline flashes across a large screen in a bustling airport lounge: "TECH MOGUL\'S DATA STOLEN IN SOPHISTICATED HEIST." Below it, a blurred, grainy image of Gabriel\'s face.]\n\n**SCENE 1 — AIRPORT LOUNGE - DAY**\n[LEILA (20s, elegant, but with a new edge) and GABRIEL (30s, intense, watchful) sit disguised amidst the travelers. Leila wears a wide-brimmed hat and oversized sunglasses. Gabriel has a fake beard and glasses. They are trying to blend in, but their tension is palpable.]\n\nLEILA\n(Whispering)\nThey\'re fast. Too fast.\n\nGABRIEL\n(Eyes scanning the room)\nJulian\'s playing a different game now. He\'s not just trying to find us. He\'s trying to turn the world against us.\n\n[Leila glances at the news screen. The blurred image of Gabriel\'s face sharpens slightly, making him more recognizable.]\n\nLEILA\nThey\'re calling you the mastermind. The "Shadow Hacker."\n\nGABRIEL\n(A grim chuckle)\nCreative. He\'s good. He knows how to hit where it hurts.\n\n**SCENE 2 — ABANDONED WAREHOUSE - NIGHT (FLASHBACK)**\n[SOUND of rapid keyboard typing, flickering monitors]\n[Gabriel, hunched over a makeshift workstation, frantically types. Leila watches over his shoulder, a map of Julian\'s data servers projected onto a wall.]\n\nLEILA\nAre you sure this is the right server? The one with the real dirt?\n\nGABRIEL\n(Without looking up)\nIt\'s the only one he hasn\'t moved since the last breach. He thinks it\'s impenetrable.\n\n[A sudden, violent SHUDDER runs through the warehouse. Dust rains down from the ceiling.]\n\nLEILA\nWhat was that?\n\nGABRIEL\n(Eyes widening)\nA resonant frequency attack. He\'s trying to fry the system.\n\n**SCENE 3 — AIRPORT LOUNGE - DAY**\n[Leila pulls her hat lower, feeling exposed. Gabriel subtly adjusts his position, creating a shield between her and the main entrance.]\n\nLEILA\nThis isn\'t just about the data, is it? He\'s making you a scapegoat.\n\nGABRIEL\n(Voice low, dangerous)\nHe\'s trying to make sure no one believes a word we say when we finally expose him. He\'s discrediting us before we even speak.\n\n[A uniformed AIRPORT SECURITY GUARD (40s, stern) walks past their table, his eyes lingering for a moment on Gabriel\'s face before moving on.]\n\nLEILA\n(Tensing)\nDid he see you?\n\nGABRIEL\n(Calmly