Gabriel sit opposite each other in a relatively empty train car. The landscape blurs past the window. Leila is sketching furiously in her notebook, a detailed drawing of the train station they just left.\n\nLEILA\n(without looking up)\nDo you think he knows we\'re on a train?\n\nGABRIEL\n(eyes scanning the car, then the window)\nJulian? He knows everything. But he won\'t expect us to be this public. It\'s a calculated risk.\n\nLEILA\n(a wry smile)\nCalculated risks. My new favorite pastime.\n\n[She finishes a detail on her sketch – a small, almost hidden camera mounted above a ticket kiosk. Gabriel leans over, his gaze following hers.]\n\n**SCENE 3 — THE SKETCHED CLUE**\n[INT. TRAIN - PASSENGER CAR - CONTINUOUS]\nGabriel studies Leila\'s sketch. He points to the tiny camera.\n\nGABRIEL\nGood eye. That\'s not standard station equipment. Too small, too well hidden.\n\nLEILA\nI saw it when we were buying tickets. Thought it was odd. Julian\'s tech?\n\nGABRIEL\nCould be. Or someone else\'s. The world is full of eyes, Leila. We just have to make sure they\'re looking in the wrong direction.\n\n[He pulls out his burner phone, quickly typing a message. A small, almost imperceptible tremor runs through his hand.]\n\n**SCENE 4 — THE UNSEEN THREAT**\n[INT. TRAIN STATION - SECURITY ROOM - DAY]\nMark watches the monitor. He sees Gabriel pull out his phone, type. Mark\'s eyes narrow.\n\nMARK\n(to himself, a low murmur)\nSmart boy. But not smart enough.\n\n[He taps a key on his console. On a separate screen, a complex algorithm begins to run, tracing Gabriel\'s signal. The red dot on the network diagram, representing Leila and Gabriel, briefly flickers, then continues its path.]\n\n**CLIFFHANGER / EPISODE END**\n[INT. TRAIN - PASSENGER CAR - DAY]\nGabriel glances back at Leila, a flicker of concern in his eyes. He pockets his phone. The train rounds a bend, plunging them into a dark tunnel. The faint light from the window vanishes, leaving them in near darkness, the rhythmic clatter of the train echoing ominously.\n\n## EPISODE 32 — The Silent Watcher\n*Duration target: 120–180 seconds*\n\n**COLD OPEN (0:00–0:15)**\n[INT. ABANDONED WAREHOUSE - NIGHT]\nA single, unblinking red light on a surveillance camera swivels slowly, tracking an empty corridor. Dust motes dance in the weak beam. The only sound is the faint, rhythmic whir of its motor.\n\n**SCENE 1 — THE PERIMETER BREACH**\n[INT. ABANDONED WAREHOUSE - CONTROL ROOM - NIGHT]\nGABRIEL (30s, intense, focused) stares at a bank of monitors, his face illuminated by the flickering screens. He sips from a lukewarm coffee. LEILA (20s, observant, tired but alert) watches him from a makeshift cot in the corner.\n\nA small, green indicator light on one of the screens flickers red. Gabriel\'s eyes narrow.\n\nGABRIEL\n(Muttering)\nSilas, you son of a...\n\nLeila sits up, instantly alert.\n\nLEILA\nWhat is it?\n\nGABRIEL\nPerimeter breach. Sector Gamma. Silas\'s blind spot.\n\n[Gabriel types furiously, bringing up a schematic of the warehouse. A small, red dot moves steadily towards their position.]\n\n**SCENE 2 — THE GHOST IN THE MACHINE**\n[INT. ABANDONED WAREHOUSE - CONTROL ROOM - CONTINUOUS]\nLeila moves to stand beside Gabriel, peering at the screen.\n\nLEILA\nWho\'s Silas? And why does he have a blind spot?\n\nGABRIEL\n(Without looking away)\nSilas is a ghost. Or was. A former comms expert. Owes me. Apparently, not enough to secure his own back door.\n\nThe red dot on the screen pauses, then moves again, faster.\n\nLEILA\nThey know we\'re here.\n\nGABRIEL\nThey know Silas was here. They\'re looking for him. We\'re just a bonus.\n\n[Gabriel pulls up another screen, showing a complex network diagram. He begins rerouting data streams, his fingers a blur.]\n\n**SCENE 3 — A FAMILIAR SHADOW**\n[INT. ABANDONED WAREHOUSE - CORRIDOR - NIGHT]\nA heavily armed FIGURE in tactical gear moves silently through the dusty corridor, illuminated by the red glow of their night vision goggles. They carry a suppressed