NE 2 — DIGITAL DEFENSE**\n[INT. RUSTIC CABIN - CONTINUOUS]\nThe drone\'s whirring GROWLS louder. Gabriel pulls out a burner phone, his fingers flying across the screen.\n\nGABRIEL\n(Into phone, terse)\nGhost, I need a diversion. Now.\n\nA faint, high-pitched SQUEAL emanates from the phone, barely audible over the drone.\n\nLEILA\nWhat are you doing?\n\nGABRIEL\nJamming their signal. Buying us time.\n\n[The drone\'s red eyes outside the window flicker erratically.]\n\n**SCENE 3 — LEILA\'S OBSERVATION**\n[INT. RUSTIC CABIN - CONTINUOUS]\nLeila peeks over the table. She sees the drone\'s erratic movements, then notices a faint, almost invisible GLOW on Gabriel\'s phone screen – a complex, rapidly changing waveform.\n\nLEILA\nIs that... a frequency signature?\n\nGabriel glances at her, a flicker of surprise in his eyes, but doesn\'t answer. He continues to type furiously.\n\nGABRIEL\n(Muttering)\nCome on, Ghost. Don\'t fail me now.\n\n**SCENE 4 — THE GHOST\'S ECHO**\n[INT. RUSTIC CABIN - CONTINUOUS]\nSuddenly, the drone outside emits a loud, distorted SHRIEK, then veers sharply away, crashing into the trees with a distant THUD.\n\nGabriel lowers the phone, exhaling slowly.\n\nGABRIEL\n(To Leila)\nThat was Ghost. She owes me.\n\nLEILA\n(Eyes wide)\nOwes you for what?\n\nGABRIEL\nA favor. And now, I owe her.\n\n**CLIFFHANGER / EPISODE END**\n[INT. RUSTIC CABIN - CONTINUOUS]\nGabriel\'s burner phone vibrates with an incoming message. He opens it. The screen displays a single, cryptic image: a blurred photo of a secure server room, with a flashing red alert icon over one of the servers. Below it, text reads: "Your turn, Varela. Mainframe access. Tonight." Gabriel\'s jaw tightens, a new, immediate threat now looming.\n\n## EPISODE 34 — The Unseen Hand\n*Duration target: 120–180 seconds*\n\n**COLD OPEN (0:00–0:15)**\n[INT. ABANDONED WAREHOUSE - NIGHT]\nA single, flickering fluorescent light illuminates a makeshift operating table. On it, a bound and gagged MARK (50s, sharp suit now torn) struggles against his restraints. A gloved hand plunges a syringe into his arm.\n\n**SCENE 1 — MARK\'S INTERROGATION**\n[INT. ABANDONED WAREHOUSE - CONTINUOUS]\nMark\'s eyes flutter open, disoriented. He tries to speak, but his jaw is slack.\n\nLEILA\n(Stepping into the light, cold and determined)\nStill think you\'re untouchable, Mark?\n\nMark\'s eyes dart around, fear replacing confusion. He tries to pull against his restraints.\n\nGABRIEL\n(Leaning against a support beam, arms crossed)\nThe truth, Mark. Or the next injection won\'t be so gentle.\n\n[Leila holds up a small vial of clear liquid. Mark\'s eyes widen in terror.]\n\n**SCENE 2 — THE COLD TRUTH**\n[INT. ABANDONED WAREHOUSE - CONTINUOUS]\nMark struggles, a guttural sound escaping his throat.\n\nLEILA\n(Voice steady, devoid of emotion)\nJulian\'s network. The shell corporations. The money laundering. We know it all. We just need your part.\n\nMark shakes his head weakly, tears welling in his eyes.\n\nGABRIEL\n(Stepping closer, his voice a low growl)\nYou helped him frame us. You helped him try to kill us. You think we\'re playing games?\n\n[Gabriel taps the syringe against the vial. Mark flinches.]\n\n**SCENE 3 — A MOTHER\'S SECRET**\n[INT. ABANDONED WAREHOUSE - CONTINUOUS]\nMark\'s eyes lock onto Leila\'s. He tries to form words, his mouth moving uselessly.\n\nLEILA\n(Softening slightly, a calculated move)\nMy mother... she trusted you. What did Julian promise you?\n\nMark\'s eyes flicker, a hint of something beyond fear in them. He points a trembling finger towards a hidden pocket inside his torn suit jacket.\n\nGABRIEL\n(Quickly patting him down)\nWhat is it?\n\n[Gabriel pulls out a small, tarnished silver locket. It\'s identical to Leila\'s, but older, more worn.]\n\n**CLIFFHANGER / EPISODE END**\n[INT. ABANDONED WAREHOUSE - CONTINUOUS]\nLeila stares at the locket in Gabriel\'s hand, her own fingers instinctively going to the one around her neck. Mark, his eyes now pleading, tries to mouth