everal monitors. GABRIEL (30s, intense) is hunched over a keyboard, his fingers flying. LEILA (20s, alert) watches him, a blanket draped over her shoulders.\n\nGABRIEL\n(Muttering)\nThey\'re trying to brute force the firewall. This isn\'t Julian\'s usual M.O.\n\nLEILA\n(Voice low)\nWho is it then? Someone else knows about us?\n\n[Gabriel shakes his head, his eyes glued to the screen. A new, more aggressive attack signature appears.]\n\nGABRIEL\nThis is \'The Ghost.\' A former comms expert. She\'s good. Too good.\n\n**SCENE 2 — THE DIGITAL DUEL**\n[INT. ABANDONED WAREHOUSE - NIGHT]\nGabriel types furiously, sweat beading on his forehead. Leila leans closer, trying to decipher the rapidly changing lines of code.\n\nLEILA\nCan you stop her?\n\nGABRIEL\n(Grimly)\nI can try. But she\'s not just after our location. She\'s trying to plant a tracker.\n\n[A red warning flashes across the screen: "ACCESS ATTEMPT: FAILED. RETRYING..."]\n\nLEILA\nA tracker? Why?\n\nGABRIEL\nTo lead Julian straight to us. Or worse, to lead him to her.\n\n**SCENE 3 — THE COST OF CONTACT**\n[INT. ABANDONED WAREHOUSE - NIGHT]\nGabriel slams his fist on the table, a frustrated grunt escaping him.\n\nGABRIEL\nDamn it. She\'s using a zero-day exploit. I need to reroute through a secure proxy. But it\'ll cost us.\n\nLEILA\nCost us what?\n\nGABRIEL\nA favor. From Silas. He\'ll want something in return. Something risky.\n\n[Gabriel pulls up a secure comms channel. A distorted, gravelly voice answers.]\n\nSILAS (O.S.)\nVarela. You sound desperate.\n\nGABRIEL\nI need a secure relay. Now. Full encryption.\n\nSILAS (O.S.)\n(Chuckles)\nAlways a rush with you. My price: a package. Cross-border. Tonight.\n\n**SCENE 4 — THE UNSEEN THREAT**\n[INT. ABANDONED WAREHOUSE - NIGHT]\nGabriel looks at Leila, a silent question in his eyes. She nods, resolute.\n\nLEILA\nWe don\'t have a choice, do we?\n\nGABRIEL\nNo. Not if we want to stay hidden.\n\n[Gabriel types a final command. The chaotic code on the screen stabilizes