NE 2 — THE CHIMERA PROJECT**\n[Gabriel pulls up a different screen, displaying a fragmented, heavily redacted document. The words "PROJECT CHIMERA" are visible at the top, along with schematics of advanced surveillance equipment and data encryption algorithms.]\n\nGABRIEL\nIt was a ghost in the system. A legend. Julian\'s most secure, most untraceable network. Designed to operate completely off-grid.\n\nLEILA\nBut we thought we disabled everything. We cut off his access.\n\nGABRIEL\nWe cut off his *known* access. This... this is something else. Something deeper.\n\n[Gabriel points to a section of the document. A name is visible, partially obscured: "A. Thorne." Leila leans closer, her breath catching.]\n\nLEILA\n"A. Thorne"? Could it be... another family member?\n\n**SCENE 3 — A NEW PLAYER**\n[Leila paces, her mind racing. Gabriel continues to work at the console, his brow furrowed in concentration.]\n\nLEILA\nHe\'s been playing us all along. He knew we\'d find the other networks. This was his fail-safe.\n\nGABRIEL\n(without looking up)\nIt\'s more than a fail-safe. It\'s an active threat. That symbol, that tone... it means they\'re not just watching. They\'re making a move.\n\n[A small, red light begins to blink erratically on a forgotten, dusty router in the corner of the room. Neither Leila nor Gabriel notice it immediately.]\n\nLEILA\nBut why show themselves now? Why warn us?\n\nGABRIEL\nBecause they want us to know. They want us to be afraid.\n\n**SCENE 4 — THE BREACH**\n[The red light on the router blinks faster, then turns solid green. A low HUM begins to emanate from the device, growing steadily louder. Gabriel finally looks up, his eyes narrowing.]\n\nGABRIEL\n(muttering)\nNo...\n\n[He lunges for the router, but it\'s too late. The hum intensifies, and suddenly, all the screens in the room flicker back to life, displaying the predatory bird symbol, its red eyes glowing menacingly. A distorted, synthesized voice fills the room, cold and utterly devoid of human emotion.]\n\nSYNTHESIZED VOICE (O.S.)\n(distorted, metallic)\nGabriel Varela. Leila Arman. Your game is over.\n\n**CLIFFHANGER / EPISODE END**\n[The synthesized voice laughs, a chilling, mechanical sound that sends shivers down Leila\'s spine. The bird symbol on the screens morphs into a countdown timer, rapidly ticking down from 00:30. Gabriel grabs Leila\'s hand, his face a mask of grim determination, pulling her towards the door as the hum of the router reaches a deafening crescendo, and the walls around them begin to vibrate.]\n\n## EPISODE 46 — The Ghost in the Machine\n\n**COLD OPEN (0:00–0:15)**\n[A single, flickering monitor in a dark room. Lines of code scroll rapidly. A hand, gloved, types furiously, then hits ENTER. The screen goes black.]\n\n**SCENE 1 — THE SILENT ALARM**\n[INT. ABANDONED WAREHOUSE - NIGHT]\n[Leila and Gabriel are hunched over a makeshift workstation. Gabriel is typing on a laptop, Leila is sketching intently on a tablet, a new, more confident stroke in her lines. Suddenly, a subtle, high-pitched BEEP sounds from Gabriel\'s wrist-mounted device.]\n\nLEILA\n(whispering)\nWhat was that?\n\nGABRIEL\n(eyes narrowing, checking device)\nA silent alarm. Old school. Means someone just tripped a perimeter sensor we didn\'t know about.\n\n[Leila’s head snaps up, her eyes scanning the shadows.]\n\n**SCENE 2 — THE GHOST\'S MESSAGE**\n[INT. ABANDONED WAREHOUSE - CONTINUOUS]\n[Gabriel pulls up a schematic on his laptop. A red dot blinks on the outer edge of the warehouse. He types quickly, then a new window pops up. It\'s a text-based message, simple, stark.]\n\nGABRIEL\n(reading aloud, grimly)\n"They know."\n\nLEILA\n(confused)\nWho knows what?\n\nGABRIEL\n(pointing to the bottom of the message)\n"The Ghost." It\'s a warning from an old contact. Someone just breached a secure location connected to Julian\'s network. And they\'re coming for us.\n\n**SCENE 3 — THE UNSEEN THREAT**\n[INT. ABANDONED WAREHOUSE - CONTINUOUS]\n[Leila looks at the blinking