s of them. All funneling money through offshore accounts. And look... a direct link to the company that supplied the drone.\n\n**SCENE 2 — MARK\'S FEAR**\nINT. MARK\'S LUXURY APARTMENT - NIGHT\n\n[MARK (40s, Julian\'s lawyer), sits at his polished desk, a half-empty glass of whiskey in his hand. His phone buzzes. He answers, his voice tight.]\n\nMARK\nYes?\n\n[Julian\'s voice, distorted and cold, comes through the speaker.]\n\nJULIAN (O.S.)\nThe network has been breached. Someone\'s digging.\n\nMARK\n(Eyes wide)\nBreached? How? I ensured the firewalls were impenetrable.\n\nJULIAN (O.S.)\nImpenetrable for amateurs. This is professional. Find out who. And make sure they regret it.\n\n[Mark swallows hard, his gaze darting nervously around his opulent, yet suddenly vulnerable, apartment.]\n\nMARK\nUnderstood.\n\n**SCENE 3 — THE TRAP IS SET**\nINT. ABANDONED WAREHOUSE - NIGHT\n\n[Leila points to a specific transaction on the screen.]\n\nLEILA\nThis one. It\'s an anomaly. A payment to a shell company that dissolved two years ago. It’s a dead drop.\n\nGABRIEL\nA message.\n\nLEILA\nOr a trap. It\'s a location. An old industrial complex on the outskirts of the city. Tomorrow, 0300.\n\n[Gabriel\'s eyes narrow. He pulls out a map on his tablet, zooming in on the location. Leila looks at him, her expression determined.]\n\nLEILA\nI\'m going with you.\n\nGABRIEL\n(Shakes his head)\nToo dangerous.\n\nLEILA\n(Steely)\nThis is my fight, Gabriel. I found the lead. I\'m seeing it through. Besides, who better to recognize Julian\'s handiwork than me?\n\n**CLIFFHANGER / EPISODE END**\n[Gabriel studies Leila\'s resolute face, then the map. He nods slowly, a flicker of reluctant approval in his eyes. He begins to gather their gear, checking his weapons. A faint, almost imperceptible RED LIGHT begins to blink on the edge of Leila\'s laptop screen, a newly activated tracker, unnoticed by them both, its signal silently broadcasting their location.]\n\n## EPISODE 48 — The Hunter\'s Trap\n*Duration target: 120–180 seconds*\n\n**COLD OPEN (0:00–0:15)**\n[Leila and Gabriel, moving through a crowded marketplace, suddenly freeze. A faint, almost imperceptible RED DOT appears on Gabriel\'s chest, then shifts to Leila\'s head. They exchange a look of grim understanding.]\n\n**SCENE 1 — THE SNIPER\'S EYE**\n[Leila and Gabriel are in a bustling, open-air marketplace. The red dot from a sniper\'s laser sight dances across Gabriel\'s chest, then Leila\'s head. They are surrounded by oblivious shoppers.]\n\nGABRIEL\n(low, urgent)\nSniper. Rooftop, northeast.\n\nLEILA\n(eyes scanning, calm despite the terror)\nHow do we move? Too exposed.\n\n[Gabriel grabs Leila\'s arm, pulling her sharply behind a fruit stall. The red dot disappears for a moment, then reappears on the stall\'s wooden frame, just inches from Leila\'s face. Gabriel pulls out a small, mirrored compact from his pocket, angling it to reflect the light. He quickly assesses the angle.]\n\nGABRIEL\nThey\'re good. Too patient for Julian\'s usual goons.\n\n**SCENE 2 — A DANGEROUS DISTRACTION**\n[Leila spots a vendor selling brightly colored balloons. An idea sparks in her eyes.]\n\nLEILA\nThe balloons. Can you create a distraction?\n\nGABRIEL\n(nods, already moving)\nStay low. When I say go, run for the alley, left side. Don\'t look back.\n\n[Gabriel quickly grabs a handful of small, heavy stones from a nearby planter. He slings them with surprising force and accuracy towards the balloon vendor\'s cart. Several balloons pop loudly, startling the vendor and causing a small commotion. Gabriel then hurls a larger stone, shattering a nearby ceramic pot. People scream, and a wave of panic ripples through the market.]\n\n**SCENE 3 — THE ESCAPE**\n[The red dot flickers, momentarily lost in the chaos. Gabriel shoves Leila forward.]\n\nGABRIEL\nGo! Now!\n\n[Leila sprints, weaving through the panicked crowd. She glances back once, seeing Gabriel drawing fire, creating a diversion. He ducks behind a larger stall, a shot ringing out and splintering the wood where he\'d been moments before. Leila forces herself to keep running, reaching the narrow alleyway.]\n\n**SCENE 4 — THE TRAP SPRINGS**\n[Leila bursts into the alley, gasping for breath. It\'s dark and smells of refuse. She looks back, expecting Gabriel. Instead, a heavy metal grate SLAMS down behind her, sealing off the alley entrance. She\'s trapped.]\n\nLEILA\nGabriel!\n\n[From the other end of the alley, a figure emerges from the shadows. It\'s MARK, Leila\'s family lawyer, impeccably dressed, a cold smile on his face. He holds a small, ornate locket in his hand – the one Anna had been clutching.]\n\nMARK\nLooking for your protector, Ms. Arman? He\'s quite busy. Julian sends his regards.\n\n**CLIFFHANGER / EPISODE END**\n[Mark holds up the locket, then casually drops it, letting it clatter to the grimy ground. Leila stares at him, then at the locket, a dawning horror on her face. The sound of distant sirens grows louder, closing in on the marketplace, leaving Leila trapped and alone with her betrayer.]\n\n## EPISODE 49 — The Ghost in the Machine\n*Duration target: 120–180 seconds*\n\n**COLD OPEN (0:00–0:15)**\n[CLOSE UP on a flickering server rack, wires snaking like veins. A single, small red light on a tiny device blinks rhythmically, almost imperceptibly, amidst the hum of machinery.]\n\n**SCENE 1 — THE DIGITAL INFILTRATION**\n[INT. SECURE SERVER FARM - NIGHT]\nThe server farm is a cold, sterile environment, rows of blinking lights reflecting in the polished floor. GABRIEL (30s, intense, focused), hunched over a laptop, his fingers flying across the keyboard. LEILA (20s, sharp, determined) stands beside him, watching the complex code scroll rapidly across the screen.\n\nLEILA\nAre you sure this is the right access point? Julian\'s security is... legendary.\n\nGABRIEL\n(Without looking up)\nHis ego is legendary. His security has blind spots, just like everyone else. This one was built by \'The Ghost.\' She owes me.\n\n[A