ed by a chilling, distorted image of Julian\'s face, smiling.]\n\n## EPISODE 50 — The Ghost in the Machine\nDuration target: 120–180 seconds\n\n**COLD OPEN (0:00–0:15)**\n[A close-up on a complex network diagram projected onto a wall, lines of code scrolling rapidly. A single, blinking red node labeled "PROJECT CHIMERA" pulses ominously.]\n\n**SCENE 1 — THE DIGITAL LABYRINTH**\n[LEILA (20s, determined) and GABRIEL (30s, focused) are in a dimly lit, makeshift server room. Gabriel is hunched over a laptop, his fingers flying across the keyboard. Leila watches the projected diagram.]\n\nLEILA\n(Whispering)\nAre you sure this is it? The core?\n\nGABRIEL\n(Without looking up)\nIt\'s a ghost in the machine. A hidden layer Julian thought no one would ever find. This is where he stored the real dirt.\n\n[Leila points to the blinking red node on the diagram.]\n\nLEILA\nProject Chimera. What is it?\n\nGABRIEL\n(Grimly)\nSomething from my past. Something I thought was buried.\n\n**SCENE 2 — THE DATA EXTRACTION**\n[Gabriel types furiously. Lines of data flash across his screen. Leila pulls up a chair next to him, her eyes scanning the raw information.]\n\nLEILA\nIt\'s all here. Shell corporations, offshore accounts... and names. High-profile names.\n\nGABRIEL\n(Nodding)\nHe didn\'t just launder money. He laundered reputations.\n\n[A sudden, sharp BEEP from Gabriel\'s laptop. A progress bar appears on screen: "DATA TRANSFER: 10%".]\n\nLEILA\nIt\'s working!\n\nGABRIEL\n(Tense)\nToo slow. Julian\'s system will detect the intrusion. We have minutes.\n\n**SCENE 3 — THE TRAP SPRINGS**\n[The server room lights flicker. A low HUM starts, growing louder. On the projected network diagram, new red lines begin to trace back towards their location, like predatory tendrils.]\n\nLEILA\nWhat\'s happening?\n\nGABRIEL\n(Eyes wide)\nHe\'s activated a counter-measure. A digital tripwire. He knows we\'re here.\n\n[The HUM intensifies. The red lines on the diagram are closing in rapidly. The data transfer bar crawls to 25%.]\n\n**CLIFFHANGER / EPISODE END**\n[A metallic CLANG from the hallway outside. The door to the server room begins to creak open, slowly, revealing only darkness. Gabriel shoves Leila behind a server rack, pulling out a silenced pistol. The data transfer is only 30% complete.]\n\n## EPISODE 51 — The Server Room Showdown\n\n**COLD OPEN (0:00–0:15)**\n[The HUM of the servers is deafening. Red lines on the diagram pulsate wildly, converging on their location. The data transfer bar is stuck at 30%.]\n\n**SCENE 1 — DIGITAL TRAP**\n[Gabriel shoves Leila behind a server rack, pulling out a silenced pistol. The door to the server room creaks open, revealing only darkness. The data transfer is still at 30%.]\n\nLEILA\n(Whispering, terrified)\nWhat\'s happening?\n\nGABRIEL\n(Eyes scanning the door, voice low)\nHe\'s activated a counter-measure. A digital tripwire. He knows we\'re here.\n\n[The HUM intensifies. The red lines on the diagram are closing in rapidly. The data transfer bar crawls to 25%.]\n\n**SCENE 2 — UNEXPECTED ALLY**\n[A figure steps into the doorway, silhouetted against the dim hallway light. It\'s ANNA, Julian\'s assistant, holding a tablet. She looks terrified.]\n\nANNA\n(Voice trembling)\nHe knows. He\'s sending security. I… I couldn\'t let him win. Not like this.\n\n[Gabriel lowers his pistol slightly, still wary. Leila stares at Anna, stunned.]\n\nLEILA\nAnna? What are you doing here?\n\nANNA\n(Eyes darting nervously)\nI saw the data transfer. He’s been tracking it. I… I have a bypass code. It’ll give you a few more minutes.\n\n**SCENE 3 — RACE AGAINST TIME**\n[Anna rushes to a nearby console, her fingers flying across the keyboard. The red lines on the diagram momentarily flicker, then resume their rapid advance. The data transfer bar inches to 32%.]\n\nGABRIEL\n(To Anna, urgently)\nHow many minutes?\n\nANNA\n(Sweat beading on her forehead)\nMaybe three. Four, if I’m lucky. But they\'re already on this floor.\n\n[A distant CLANG of heavy boots echoes from the hallway. Leila looks at Gabriel, then at the agonizingly slow data transfer.]\n\n**CLIFFHANGER / EPISODE END**\n[The data transfer bar reaches 35%. The heavy boots are closer now, growing louder. Gabriel shoves Anna towards a service tunnel exit, then turns back to Leila, his eyes grim. "We\'re out of time. We need to go. Now." Leila looks at the screen, then back at Gabriel, torn between escape and the unfinished data transfer. The server room door bursts open, revealing two armed SECURITY GUARDS.]\n\n## EPISODE 52 — The Ghost in the Machine\nDuration target: 120–180 seconds\n\n**COLD OPEN (0:00–0:15)**\n[A close-up on a complex, glowing server rack. A single, almost imperceptible red light blinks rhythmically. The hum of the servers is the only sound.]\n\n**SCENE 1 — THE SERVER ROOM**\n[LEILA (30s, determined, focused) and GABRIEL (40s, intense, vigilant) are hunched over a laptop connected to the server rack. The data transfer bar on the screen is at 35%.]\n\nLEILA\n(Whispering)\nIt’s too slow. We don’t have enough time.\n\nGABRIEL\n(Eyes scanning the door)\nWe have to make time. This is our only shot at the full ledger.\n\n[A distant THUD echoes from the hallway. Gabriel’s head snaps up.]\n\nLEILA\nWhat was that?\n\nGABRIEL\n(Grim)\nJulian’s private security. They’re here.\n\n**SCENE 2 — THE ESCAPE ROUTE**\n[ANNA (30s, pale, trembling) huddles by a small, grimy service tunnel exit, her face etched with fear.]\n\nANNA\n(Voice barely audible)\nThey’ll kill us all. Julian doesn’t leave witnesses.\n\nGABRIEL\n(To Anna, sharply)\nThen don’t be a witness. Go. Now.\n\n[Gabriel shoves Anna towards the tunnel entrance. She hesitates, looking back at Leila.]\n\nANNA\nLeila, please—\n\nLEILA\n(Without looking up from the screen)\nGo, Anna! Get out!\n\n[Anna, tears streaming, scrambles into the dark tunnel.]\n\n**SCENE 3 — THE IMPENDING BREACH**\n[The data transfer bar crawls to 38%. The heavy boots from the hallway are closer now, growing louder, echoing ominously.]\n\nLEILA\n(Muttering to herself)\nCome on, come on…\n\nGABRIEL\n(Standing, pulling out a silenced pistol)\nLeila, we have to go. It’s not worth it.\n\nLEILA\n(Eyes fixed on the screen)\nIt is. It’s everything. This is the proof.\n\n[The server room door begins to rattle violently.]\n\n**CLIFFHANGER / EPISODE END**\n[The data transfer bar reaches 40%. The server room door bursts open, revealing two armed SECURITY GUARDS in tactical gear, their weapons raised. Gabriel fires a single, precise shot, dropping one guard, but the other immediately opens fire. Gabriel shoves Leila towards the tunnel, but she glances back at the laptop, then at the second guard advancing. The screen flickers, showing a new, encrypted message appearing over the transfer bar: "SYSTEM OVERRIDE DETECTED. DATA PURGE INITIATED." Leila\'s eyes widen in horror.]\n\nEPISODE 53 — The System Override\n\n**COLD OPEN (0:00–0:15)**\n[CLOSE UP on the laptop screen. The data transfer progress bar for "Operation Chimera" is stuck at 40%. A new, encrypted message flashes over it: "SYSTEM OVERRIDE DETECTED. DATA PURGE INITIATED." Leila\'s eyes widen in horror.]\n\n**SCENE 1 — Server Room Chaos**\n[The server room is a maelstrom of flashing lights and blaring alarms. The second SECURITY GUARD, having recovered from Gabriel\'s initial shot, fires wildly. Gabriel shoves LEILA towards the tunnel entrance, his face a mask of grim determination.]\n\nGABRIEL\n(shouting over the alarms)\nGo! Now!\n\n[Leila hesitates, glancing back at the laptop screen, then at the advancing guard. The data purge accelerates, numbers blurring.]\n\nLEILA\n(panicked)\nThe data! It\'s deleting!\n\n[Gabriel fires another shot, forcing the guard to duck, buying them a precious second. He grabs Leila\'s arm, pulling her towards the tunnel.]\n\nGABRIEL\nIt\'s gone! We have to move!\n\n**SCENE 2 — Tunnel Escape**\n[Gabriel and Leila scramble through the narrow, dusty tunnel. The sounds of gunfire and alarms from the server room echo behind them, growing fainter. Leila coughs, dust clinging to her hair.]\n\nLEILA\n(gasping)\nWhat was that? "System override"?\n\nGABRIEL\n(pushing her forward)\nJulian\'s fail-safe. He knew we\'d come for the data.\n\n[Leila stumbles, catching herself on the rough-hewn wall. Her mind races, replaying the flashing message.]\n\nLEILA\nBut... "Data purge initiated"? He destroyed his own evidence?\n\nGABRIEL\nHe\'d rather burn it all than let us have it. It\'s a scorched-earth tactic.\n\n[They reach a junction. Gabriel pauses, listening intently to the distant sounds.]\n\nGABRIEL\nHe\'s buying time. For what, I don\'t know.\n\n**SCENE 3 — A Desperate Call**\n[They emerge into a dimly lit, abandoned utility corridor. Gabriel pulls out a burner phone, his fingers flying across the keypad. He puts it to his ear, listening.]\n\nGABRIEL\n(into phone, urgent)\nIt\'s Varela. We\'ve got a problem. Julian\'s system initiated a full data purge. I need to know what else he\'s got. Any other servers? Off-site backups?\n\n[He listens, his expression darkening. Leila watches him, her heart pounding. She sees the frustration etched on his face.]\n\nGABRIEL\n(into phone)\nUnderstood. Keep digging. And watch your six. He\'s cornered.\n\n[He snaps the phone shut, running a hand through his hair.]\n\nLEILA\nWhat did they say?\n\nGABRIEL\nOur contact says Julian\'s network is going dark. He\'s pulling everything offline. It\'s like he\'s trying to disappear.\n\n**SCENE 4 — The Impasse**\n[They reach a heavy, reinforced door, an exit to the outside. Gabriel tries the handle, but it\'s locked solid. He kicks it, but it doesn\'t budge.]\n\nGABRIEL\nDammit. He sealed the exits.\n\nLEILA\n(looking around, desperate)\nThere has to be another way out. He can\'t just trap us here.\n\nGABRIEL\nHe\'s not trying to trap us. He\'s trying to delay us. Give him time to vanish.\n\n[Suddenly, a faint, rhythmic BEEPING sound starts, growing louder. It\'s coming from the wall beside the door