\n\nLEILA\nGabriel, the schematics! There\'s a maintenance tunnel behind that wall, it leads directly to the vault\'s access panel!\n\nGABRIEL\n(Scanning the pipes)\nIt\'s a long shot. They\'ll have it reinforced.\n\nLEILA\nIt\'s our only shot! While they\'re focused on the door, we go through the wall.\n\n[Gabriel nods, pulling a small, powerful cutting tool from his pack. He begins to carve a rough circle into the metal wall, sparks flying.]\n\n**SCENE 4 — THE VAULT\'S DEFENSE**\n[INT. MARK\'S HIDEOUT - CONTINUOUS]\n[Mark watches the thermal images with growing panic. He sees Gabriel cutting into the wall.]\n\nMARK\n(Screaming into the comms)\nThey\'re trying to cut through! Deploy the gas!\n\n[The technician hesitates.]\n\nTECHNICIAN\nSir, that\'s a Class-A neurotoxin. It could be lethal.\n\nMARK\n(Voice rising to a fever pitch)\nI don\'t care! They cannot get into that vault! Do it!\n\n**CLIFFHANGER / EPISODE END**\n[Gabriel finishes cutting the circle. He kicks the section of metal inward, revealing a dark, narrow tunnel. Just as he and Leila prepare to enter, a faint, HISSING sound begins to emanate from within the tunnel, accompanied by a sickly sweet, acrid smell. Leila coughs, her eyes watering. Gabriel shoves her forward, covering his mouth and nose, his eyes wide with alarm.]\n\n## EPISODE 55 — The Digital Ghost Hunt\n\n**COLD OPEN (0:00–0:15)**\n[Leila stares intently at a complex network diagram projected onto a screen, her finger tracing a web of connections. Gabriel watches her, a subtle flicker of pride in his eyes. A small, almost imperceptible GLITCH ripples across the screen.]\n\n**SCENE 1 — THE GHOST IN THE MACHINE**\n[INT. ABANDONED WAREHOUSE - NIGHT]\n[Leila and Gabriel are hunched over a makeshift command center. The screen displays a constantly shifting, intricate network map of Julian\'s digital infrastructure. Leila points to a cluster of nodes.]\n\nLEILA\nThis is where he\'s hiding it. The ghost server. It\'s too well-insulated. Every time