We\'re ghosts now. And everyone\'s hunting us."\nCharacter Action: Gabriel articulates their new, dire reality.\nEmotional Shift: Primal fear, grim acceptance.\n\n## EPISODE 31: Gabriel\'s Contact Betrays Their Location\nBeat Type: Hook\n1.  Gabriel, mid-conversation with a seemingly trusted contact on a secure line, sees a flicker of fear in the contact\'s eyes just before the line goes dead. A cold dread washes over him.\nCharacter Action: Gabriel witnesses his contact\'s betrayal.\nEmotional Shift: Immediate dread, dawning realization.\n\nBeat Type: Escalation\n2.  Gabriel frantically attempts to re-establish the connection. The signal is jammed. His worst fears about the contact\'s sudden silence are confirmed.\nCharacter Action: Gabriel confirms the betrayal.\nEmotional Shift: Frantic urgency, strategic re-evaluation.\n\nBeat Type: Character Action\n3.  Leila, observing Gabriel\'s sudden shift in demeanor, instinctively grabs her bag. Her eyes scan their temporary safe house for any sign of intrusion.\nCharacter Action: Leila prepares for immediate flight.\nEmotional Shift: Heightened alertness, growing anxiety.\n\nBeat Type: Escalation\n4.  A distant siren wails, growing rapidly louder. Their compromised position is confirmed. Gabriel must make a split-second decision.\nCharacter Action: Gabriel recognizes the imminent threat.\nEmotional Shift: Urgent resolve, desperate necessity.\n\nBeat Type: Reversal\n5.  Gabriel shoves a burner phone into Leila\'s hand. He gives her terse instructions: delete all data if they\'re separated. His voice is tight with urgency.\nCharacter Action: Gabriel prepares Leila for potential separation.\nEmotional Shift: Protective instinct, grim determination.\n\nBeat Type: Quiet Beat with Teeth\n6.  The sirens blare closer. Gabriel pulls Leila into a hidden crawl space, their bodies pressed together. The tension is palpable. His hand instinctively covers her mouth as heavy footsteps echo outside.\nCharacter Action: Gabriel conceals them, enforcing silence.\nEmotional Shift: Primal fear, forced intimacy.\n\nBeat Type: Meaning Shift\n7.  Leila realizes the \'safe house\' was a trap all along. The sense of temporary peace shatters into immediate danger.\nCharacter Action: Leila re-evaluates their situation.\nEmotional Shift: Crushing betrayal, acute vulnerability.\n\nBeat Type: Cliffhanger\n8.  CLIFFHANGER: The door to their safe house bursts open with a violent crash. A flashlight beam sweeps across the room, narrowly missing their hidden location. A gruff voice barks, "Clear! They\'re not here... yet."\nCharacter Action: An unknown assailant confirms their escape, but their presence is known.\nEmotional Shift: Terrified relief, lingering dread.\n\n## EPISODE 32: Leila Navigates the Sewer System\'s Labyrinth\nBeat Type: Hook\n1.  Gabriel shoves a heavy grate aside, revealing a dark, foul-smelling sewer tunnel. He urges a hesitant Leila to descend into the unknown.\nCharacter Action: Gabriel forces a difficult choice.\nEmotional Shift: Disgust, profound reluctance.\n\nBeat Type: Character Action\n2.  Leila, gagging from the stench, hesitates. Gabriel\'s urgent gaze pushes her forward. She confronts her deepest fears of claustrophobia and filth.\nCharacter Action: Leila overcomes her aversion.\nEmotional Shift: Resigned determination, mounting anxiety.\n\nBeat Type: Escalation\n3.  They navigate the narrow, slimy tunnels in near darkness. Echoing drips and scuttling sounds amplify Leila\'s anxiety. Her hand clutches Gabriel\'s arm for reassurance.\nCharacter Action: Leila seeks comfort amidst fear.\nEmotional Shift: Heightened fear, physical discomfort.\n\nBeat Type: Subtext Scene\n4.  Leila wants to voice her disgust and fear but won\'t. She asks, "Are you sure this is the only way?" Her trembling grip on Gabriel\'s arm is her tell. Gabriel wants to reassure her but can\'t risk slowing down. He says, "Keep moving." His rapid, searching glances around the tunnel are his tell.\nCharacter Action: Leil